      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLASSIC ETHICS (1) finished sixth last time at Richmond but could not have been more impressive before that in his swift 34.66 win at Gosford over 603m. Has the ability and expected to go close again. FASTENED (2) goes very well this trip starting eight times for three wins and two minors. Below best last time at this track (29.99) in a NG, finishing a 6 length fifth. Among the main chances. WONDER I DO (8) tends to drift back and work into the race, finishing out of the placings two back before charging home into the minors latest when second (24.82) in a Grade 5 at Maitland last time. Has a good record at this journey. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Bold showing expected. FLASH ON BY (3) is a last-start placegetter who should be thereabouts.",
